  <h2>Nail Fungus</h2>
 <p>
Onychomycosis is a fungal infection of the finger or toe nails which can be difficult to cure.

Onychomycosis is caused by a fungus. Often a person could have had athlete's foot for a long time prior to the development of onychomycosis.
Also, in some cases trauma or damage to a nail may contribute to the development of onychomycosis.<br><br>

Onychomycosis of the finger nails can be treated by taking a prescription medication called griseofulvin. Griseofulvin however, does come with side effects.
A new medication, terbinafine, is now available for the treatment of toe and finger nail fungal infections. Terbinafine is taken once a day for 6 to 12 weeks. This medication has fewer side effects than griseofulvin.<br><br>
Other topical treatments are also available.

